summary: In which you tie your tail to your Valentine’s for the day.  Also a list as to what the flowers mean that were chosen for...
caption:
In which you tie your tail to your Valentine’s for the day. 

Also a list as to what the flowers mean that were chosen for Snufkin and Moomin!

For the ones that were given to Moomin from Snufkin:
Yellow Tulips (Joy)
Pink calla lilies (Admiration and appreciation)
Daisies (Innocence and a new beginning) 
Lilies of the valley (Purity, happiness, sweetness)
White and blue rose (Young love, loyalty, uniqueness and being wonderful)

Those given to Snufkin from Moomin:
Purple dahlia (grace, perfection, dignity, travel)
Orange Amaryllis (happiness, freedom, harmony)
Purple and blue Anemones (Anticipation, luck, protection)
Lilacs (first love) were plucked apart
Yello rose (Warmth, delight, affection, “welcome back” and “remember me”)

So if The Mymble is an amphibious humanoid creature does that mean she has so many kids at once because she lays huge blobs of eggs like frogs?

And if so does that mean all mymble babies start as tadpoles? Mymbpoles!? :0

(And is Snufkin different because he’s half cat? Or was he a weird fuzzy mymbpole when he was little?)
